These fourteen (14) individual elements of the Lexington LP Terminal's prevention program work together to prevent/mitigate accidental chemical releases. The company and its employees are committed to the standards required by these management programs. In addition to the above elements, the Lexington LP Terminal utilizes specific prevention measures that are employed as part of its operating procedures along with engineering/administrative controls to help quickly detect, contain/control, and reduce the consequences of a release. These are briefly summarized as follows:

General Risk Reduction and Safety Measures

-Engineering and construction in accordance with recognized industry and corporate standards (ex. NFPA 58);
-Equipment properly designed with protection from overpressure (pressure safety relief valves, etc.);
-Updated technical drawings, Piping & Instrumentation Diagrams and Process/Block Flow Diagrams;
-Operating systems monitored and controlled by trained Operators;
-Redundant control systems with UPS;
-Automatic and manual shutdown devices for critical systems;
-Scheduled inspection and testing of instruments, analyzers, safety devices, and other critical equipment;
-Controlled facility access;
-Regular safety meetings and safety awareness programs;
-Routinely scheduled safety compliance inspections and audits; and
-Frequent process surveillance by site operations.

